    "ExtraInfo": "In a trust alliance member autonomous system (AS), an AS control server (ACS) communicates with AS edge routers (AERs) so that the ACS can send the trust alliance member list, IPv6 address prefixes, and tag information to the AERs. The ACS and AERs exchange SMA protocol packets to deploy functions, query information, and respond to requests. To view SMA protocol packet statistics, run the display sma statistics command on an AER.\nIn VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS."
